cache.description:
Optional, indicates whether the task uses caching, default is true;
After the first recognition, the subsequent recognition will always be carried out only in the location of the first recognition, enabling this can greatly save performance
But it is only appliable for tasks where the target position will not change at all, if the target position to be recognised will change, please set it to false

fullMatch.description:
Optional, whether the text recognition needs to match all the words (can't match more than one word), the default is false
false, as long as a substring can be found: for example, text: ["Start"], the actual recognition of "Start action" is also considered successful;
true, it must recognise "Start", not one word more
